    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-01-23T10:18:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-01-23T09:35:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <head>30. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d30fn1"
                        >Source: Ford Library, National Security Adviser, Memoranda of
                        Conversations, Box 8, January 23, 1975, <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1"
                            >Ford</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>.
                        Secret; <gloss target="#t_Nodis_1">Nodis</gloss>. The meeting was held in
                        the Oval Office.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1975-01-23T09:35:00-05:00" to="1975-01-23T10:18:00-05:00"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date">January 23, 1975, 9:35–10:18
                            a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>President <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1">Ford</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Dr. <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>, Secretary
                        of State and Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs</item>
                    <item>Lt. General <persName corresp="#p_SBA_1">Brent Scowcroft</persName>,
                        Deputy Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of issues unrelated to intelligence.]</p>
                <p>[<persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>:] We had a 40 Committee
                        meeting.<note n="2" xml:id="d30fn2">No record of the meeting has been
                        found.</note> We can’t conduct covert operations. <persName
                        corresp="#p_CWE_1">Colby</persName> is a disaster and really should be
                    replaced. <persName corresp="#p_CWE_1">Colby</persName> is shellshocked—he
                    wanted to testify on Azorian because it was <pb facs="0112" n="65"
                        xml:id="pg_65"/> a domestic operation.<note n="3" xml:id="d30fn3">AZORIAN
                        was the codename for the <hi rend="italic">Glomar Explorer</hi> project to
                        raise a sunken Soviet submarine. For documentation, see <ref
                            target="frus1969-76v35#d182">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations,</hi> 1969–1976, vol. XXXV, National
                            Security Policy, 1973–1976, Documents 182</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1969-76v35#d208">208</ref>.</note> He said he would work it
                    out with the <gloss target="#t_VP_1">VP</gloss>—I said it was none of the <gloss
                        target="#t_VP_1">VP</gloss>’s business.</p>
                <p>The President: That’s stupid.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>: There are now so many people
                    who have to be briefed on covert operations, it is bound to leak.</p>
                <p>There is no one with guts left. All of yesterday they were making a record to
                    protect themselves about Azorian. It was a discouraging meeting. I wonder if we
                    shouldn’t get the leadership in and discuss it. Maybe there should be a Joint
                    Committee.</p>
                <p>The President: I have always fought that, but maybe we have to. It would have to
                    be a tight group, not a big broad one.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>: I am really worried. We are
                    paralyzed. We have delayed a long time [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not
                        declassified</hi>] even though our capacity may not be too great.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of topics unrelated to intelligence.]</p>
            </div>
